(* ::Package:: *)

(* ::Chapter:: *)
(*Supplementary file to 'Third post-Newtonian dynamics for eccentric orbits and aligned spins in the effective-one-body waveform model SEOBNRv5EHM'*)


(* ::Text:: *)
(*by Aldo Gamboa, Mohammed Khalil, and Alessandra Buonanno*)
(**)
(*This file contains:*)
(*1) the 3PN waveform modes for eccentric orbits in EOB coordinates / Keplerian parametrization*)
(*2) the 3PN eccentricity corrections to the SEOBNRv5 waveform modes*)
(**)
(*When expressed in the EOB coordinates (r,pr,\[Phi],L), the (instantaneous) modes are factored as*)
(*h[l, m] = 8 M \[Nu] / R Sqrt[\[Pi]/5] E^(-i m \[Phi]) HinstEOB[l, m]*)
(**)
(*When expressed in the Keplerian parameters (x, e, \[Zeta]), the modes are factored as*)
(*h[l, m] = 8 M \[Nu] / R Sqrt[\[Pi]/5] E^(-i m \[Phi]) x H[l, m]*)
(**)
(*with H[l, m] split into instantaneous, tail, oscillatory memory, and DC memory contributions*)
(*H[l, m] = HinstKep[l, m] + HtailKep[l, m] + HmemOscKep[l, m] + HmemDCKep[l, m]*)
(**)
(*The tail and memory contributions are expanded in eccentricity to O(e^6). *)
(*We also provide eccentricity-resummed expressions for the tail and oscillatory memory contributions*)
(**)
(*Notation:*)
(*We use geometric units with c = G = 1*)
(*\[Nu] = m1 m2 / M^2 is the symmetric mass ratio*)
(*\[Delta] = (m1 - m2) / M is the antisymmetric mass ratio*)
(*M = m1 + m2 is the total mass*)
(**)
(*\[Epsilon] = 1 is a PN counting parameter*)
(*SO = 1 is a spin order counting parameter*)
(**)
(*r is the EOB relative separation*)
(*pr is the EOB radial momentum (not tortoise momentum)*)
(*L = pphi is the angular momentum*)
(**)
(*x = <M \[CapitalOmega]>^(2/3), where \[CapitalOmega] is the azimuthal orbital frequency, and <> denotes the orbit average*)
(*e is the eccentricity in the Keplerian parametrization*)
(*ei is the initial value of eccentricity for the DC memory contributions to the modes*)
(*\[Zeta] is the relativistic anomaly*)
(**)
(*\[Chi]1 = S1 / m1^2, and \[Chi]2 = S2 / m2^2 are the dimensionless spins*)
(*\[Chi]S = 1/2 (\[Chi]1 + \[Chi]2)*)
(*\[Chi]A = 1/2 (\[Chi]1 - \[Chi]2)*)
(*\[Kappa]1 and \[Kappa]2 are the spin quadrupole constants, which equal 1 for black holes*)
(*\[Kappa]S = 1/2 ((\[Kappa]1 - 1) \[Chi]1^2 + (\[Kappa]2 - 1) \[Chi]2^2)*)
(*\[Kappa]A = 1/2 ((\[Kappa]1 - 1) \[Chi]1^2 - (\[Kappa]2 - 1) \[Chi]2^2)*)
(**)
(*\[Alpha] and \[Beta] are gauge constants appearing in the leading-order RR force*)
(*(\[Alpha] = -16/3, \[Beta] = -13/2 for SEOBNRv5EHM)*)
(**)
(*x0 = Sqrt[E]/2, where E is Euler's number*)
(*r0 = 1/x0*)
(*x0p = E^(11/18 - 2/3 EulerGamma - 4/3 Log[2] + 2/3 Log[x0])*)
(*EulerGammaRedefined = E^(-11/12 + EulerGamma + 2 Log[2]) *)
(*are constants that appear in the calculation of the fluxes and modes*)


(* ::Section::Closed:: *)
